Subject: drm/i915/gen8+: Add RC6 CTX corruption WA
Git-commit: 7e34f4e4aad3fd34c02b294a3cf2321adf5b4438
Patch-mainline: v5.4-rc8
References: CVE-2019-0154 bsc#1135966 CVE-2019-0155 bsc#1135967 bnc#1151927 5.3.11

In some circumstances the RC6 context can get corrupted. We can detect
this and take the required action, that is disable RC6 and runtime PM.
The HW recovers from the corrupted state after a system suspend/resume
cycle, so detect the recovery and re-enable RC6 and runtime PM.

v2: rebase (Mika)
v3:
- Move intel_suspend_gt_powersave() to the end of the GEM suspend
  sequence.
- Add commit message.
v4:
